    "summary": "\u2022 A specialist in Islamic architecture and arts from the universities of Syria, Egypt, and the Netherlands\n\u2022 More than 20 years of experience as an archaeologist and researcher in Egypt, Syria, and the Netherlands \u200f\u2022 More than 15 years of experience in developing archaeological and tourist areas and projects for the restoration and revitalization of cultural heritage sites in Syria and Egypt\n\u2022 Proven successful track record in leadership positions, as Director of Archaeological Research and Training, Damascus, Syria, as the head of the national team responsible for registering the Dead Cities (a Syrian archaeological site) and several pertinent national and international restoration and rehabilitation projects\n\u2022 I held leadership positions in numerous scientific and academic institutions and supervised many doctoral and master's theses. I have published many books, studies, and articles on the archeology, restoration, and rehabilitation of cultural heritage areas and their relationship to national identity.\n\u2022 Doctorate and academic titles recognized by the Dutch Ministry of Higher Education\n\u2022 Founder of the Arabic-Dutch Cultural House in the Netherlands I am a research fellow at the Netherlands Institute for Advanced Studies in the Humanities and Social Sciences, Amsterdam, the Netherlands.\n\u2022 Head of the Department of Islamic Antiquities in Syria's Encyclopedia of the Antiquities Authority.",
